apps/web/src/content/docs/docs/tools/dashboard.mdx:248:Dashboard can display runs pushed to a remote git repository by other machines or CI alongside your local runs. Each run in the list carries a source badge: **local** (green) or **remote** (amber). For in-progress eval durability before final publish, AgentV writes [WIP checkpoints](/docs/tools/wip-checkpoints/) to `agentv/inflight/...` branches; Dashboard lists them only after they are recovered locally or published to the normal results branch.
apps/web/src/content/docs/docs/tools/dashboard.mdx:270:`results.repo_path: .` stores completed run artifacts on a dedicated branch of the source repository without checking out that branch in the source worktree. The branch defaults to `agentv/results/v1` for `repo_path` configs. AgentV creates the branch automatically on first publish and commits only `.agentv/results/**` paths into it. `sync.auto_push: false` keeps the result commit local; set it to `true` to push the branch best-effort after each completed run. `sync.require_push: true` is for CI workflows where a push failure should fail the command after local artifacts are written.
apps/web/src/content/docs/docs/tools/dashboard.mdx:348:There is no separate `agentv results remote status` or `agentv results remote sync` command. The `agentv results` CLI stays focused on local run workspaces; manual remote exchange is Dashboard/API-only, with eval auto-export covering the common CI/publisher path.
